name: EUTOPIA
description: When Thomas More coined the term utopia, he derived it from the Greek ou(not) and topos(place). His was a perfect idealised world: a non-existing place. But it was also a play with the pronunciation of EUTOPIA (from Greek “good place”), which is possible: we have now all the tools, science and technology necessary to build a better civilisation, to manage the common resources of humanity and all life and not only preserve but also restore our planet. @renatachebel 1080x1080px 2021
